{"document":{"format":"pptx","filename":"/Users/mark/dev/sunholo/docparse/data/test_files/poi_comment.pptx","metadata":{"title":"Water Finance","author":"Antonio Vives","created":"1998-11-20T16:31:11Z","modified":"2007-10-23T07:18:55Z","pageCount":0},"blocks":[{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"Local conditions","style":"none","level":0}]},{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"Project preparation","level":1},{"type":"text","text":"One of the major obstacles to water and sanitation finance is project preparation","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Low institutional capacity","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"A local affair, sometimes removed from decision making centers","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Difficult political and economic conditions","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Scarcity of financial resources: users, taxpayers, markets","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Project preparation not given the key role","style":"body","level":0}]},{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"Outline of the presentation","level":1},{"type":"text","text":"Project preparation","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Project structuring","style":"body","level":0}]},{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"Project structuring","level":1},{"type":"text","text":"Financial structures adapted to local realities","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Exploit all possibilities to maximize synergies between scarce resources: own labor, tariffs, donors, multilaterals, public and private resources","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"At one extreme, cooperatives, water microenterprises, municipal utilities","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"In the middle, management contracts, for operation, maintenance, collections, etc.","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"At the other extreme, full-fledged concessions","style":"body","level":0}]},{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"NEEDS","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Preparation","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Structuring","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Financing","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Project finance cycle","style":"none","level":0}]},{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"Project preparation","level":1},{"type":"text","text":"Donors and multilaterals financial institutions must emphasize support for the early stage.","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"We at the IDB hope to approve on Monday a Project Preparation Fund with grants for capacity building and project preparation","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Donors should consider “debt for water swaps” as part of their official assistance.","style":"body","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Both would leverage other funds: “teach them how to fish instead of giving them fish”","style":"body","level":0}]},{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"Removing financing obstacles through project structuring","level":1},{"type":"text","text":"Antonio Vives","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Manager, a.i.","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Sustainable Development Department","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Inter-American Development Bank","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"Access toFinancefor Local Governments","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"IV WorldWaterForum","style":"none","level":0},{"type":"text","text":"March 17, 2006","style":"none","level":0}]},{"type":"section","kind":"slide","blocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"In summary","level":1},{"type":"text","text":"Project preparation and structuring may not be a source of funds, but can help bring 